e_ops.go` defines broad cross-domain runtime structs that are reused by importer/workflow/rectify, so each consumer inherits many callbacks beyond its core responsibility.","`importer/importer.go` and `shipworkflow/operations_runtime.go` both validate long callback lists manually, showing abstraction cost has shifted to defensive wiring rather than simpler domain contracts.","`rectify/rectify.go` and `startuporchestrator/startup_orchestrator.go` layer additional runtime composition/merge logic on top of these bundles, increasing maintenance surface for every seam rename or new callback."],"suggestion":"Refactor runtime seams into smaller capability interfaces per use-case (for example, `UrbitConfigMutator`, `ContainerLifecycle`, `TransitionPublisher`) and inject only those into each subsystem. Replace manual nil-check lists with grouped interface assertions so adding/removing callbacks does not require synchronized edits across multiple runtime builders and validators.","confidence":"high","impact_scope":"codebase","fix_scope":"architectural_change","root_cause_cluster":"runtime_callback_bundle_overgrowth"},{"dimension":"abstraction_fitness","identifier":"broadcast_passthrough_wrapper_chain","summary":"Broadcast state access is split across overlapping wrappers that add call depth but little policy.","related_files":["broadcast/state.go","broadcast/transitions.go","rectify/rectify.go","leak/broadcast.go"],"evidence":["`broadcast/state.go` package-level functions largely proxy to `resolveBroadcastStateRuntime()` and then call same-named methods on `broadcastStateRuntime`.","`broadcast/transitions.go` introduces another runtime resolver (`resolveBroadcastStateTransitionRuntime`) and optional variadic runtime injection path over the same store behavior.","Callers in `rectify/rectify.go` and `leak/broadcast.go` rely on broadcast state transitions/updates, but policy is distributed between wrapper layers rather than a single explicit state service API."],"suggestion":"Co